d · tmux/tmux Wiki · GitHub\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://github.com/tmux/tmux/wiki/Getting-Started\\\"}]\\n\\nI found relevant search results for your query about tmux terminal sizing issues in headless CI environments. Here's what I found:\\n\\n## Key Issues Found\\n\\nThere's a known issue where tmux cannot resize sessions programmatically in headless environments—if you create a new session, detach from it, try to resize it, then dump the buffer, the session will still have the size of the terminal that created it.\\n\\nOne solution suggested is that the new-session tmux command needs to have the ability to be passed the -x and -y options so that a headless window of size larger than the default 80x24 can be created. This is particularly relevant for TUI applications that may fail with errors like \\\"create pane failed: pane too small\\\" in headless CI environments.\\n\\n## Related Issues\\n\\n- A feature proposal exists to add an option to the attach command to resize the current client terminal window to adapt to the size of the virtual pane being attached to, using the CSI 8 ; height ; width t escape sequence.\\n\\n- The use case involves running a program headlessly within tmux and periodically capturing output, while maintaining the ability to resize the terminal view on occasion.\\n\\nThe GitHub issues linked in the search results (particularly #1367 and #4449 in the tmux/tmux repository) may contain additional discussion and workarounds for this problem.\\n\\n\\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"8ebb69e7-490f-480e-a06e-6fc811880627\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T15:43:47.948Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"query\":\"tmux headless CI terminal size not working TUI application resize pane github actions\",\"results\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"srvtoolu_01D8mgEgP15yE6t6kW3LF79y\",\"content\":[{\"title\":\"Headlessly resizing tmux window/session · Issue #1367 · tmux/tmux\",\"url\":\"https://gith