e larger than the default 80x24 can be created. This is particularly relevant for TUI applications that may fail with errors like \\\"create pane failed: pane too small\\\" in headless CI environments.\\n\\n## Related Issues\\n\\n- A feature proposal exists to add an option to the attach command to resize the current client terminal window to adapt to the size of the virtual pane being attached to, using the CSI 8 ; height ; width t escape sequence.\\n\\n- The use case involves running a program headlessly within tmux and periodically capturing output, while maintaining the ability to resize the terminal view on occasion.\\n\\nThe GitHub issues linked in the search results (particularly #1367 and #4449 in the tmux/tmux repository) may contain additional discussion and workarounds for this problem.\"],\"durationSeconds\":8.861269374999218},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"59c6cba6-ec42-48bd-91e1-4ef1a2550da9\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"8ebb69e7-490f-480e-a06e-6fc811880627\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_experiments\",\"sessionId\":\"e24bec4f-0ec1-4a86-bc8d-b2082f315a38\",\"version\":\"2.1.66\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/fix-droid-e2e-setup\",\"slug\":\"temporal-foraging-volcano\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_018KxkRYvxXUVj7Svbx5qbyN\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01AZwNFMvhLMacZHzddmv3tG\",\"name\":\"WebFetch\",\"input\":{\"url\":\"https://github.com/tmux/tmux/issues/1367\",\"prompt\":\"What are the solutions/workarounds for resizing a detached tmux session headlessly? How do you create a tmux session with a specific size when there's no terminal attached?\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":888,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":129052,\"output_tokens\":123,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":888,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYiJBDVKpAuR7xdCF5BwS\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"157dfc4a-fad5-431b-b375-4cd9495a14ce\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T15:43:52.279Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"157dfc4a-fad5-431b-b375-4cd9495a14ce\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_experiments\",\"sessionId\":\"e24bec4f-0ec1-4a86-bc8d-b2082f315a38\",\"version\":\"2.1.66\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/fix-droid-e2e-setup\",\"slug\":\"temporal-foraging-volcano\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01AZwNFMvhLMacZHzddmv3tG\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"# Resizing Detached tmux Sessions Headlessly\\n\\nBased on the GitHub issue #1367, here are the key findings:\\n\\n## The Problem\\nWhen a tmux session is detached, programmatic resize commands don't take effect until the session is reattached. The maintainer (nicm) explained: \\\"Resize happens on attach, not on detach. There is no way to explicitly set a size on an unattached session.\\\"\\n\\n## Proposed Solution\\nThe maintainer suggested using `force-width` and `force-height` parameters to set dimensions on unattached sessions immediately, without requiring an attach/detach cycle. The approach would be: \\\"make force-width/force-height set the size of any unattached sessions immediately.\\\"\\n\\n## Practical Workarounds\\nThe issue describes several attempted approaches:\\n- Using `resize-pane` with `-x` and `-y` flags\\n- Setting `aggressive-resize`, `force-height`, and `force-width` options\\n- Attempting to use `main-pane-height` and `main-pane-width`\\n\\nHowever, none of these achieve persistent sizing without reattachment.\\n\\n## Key Limitation\\nThe fundamental constraint is that tmux doesn't support explicit size specification for fully detached sessions without some form of client connection to trigger the resize operation.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"27ee9bd0-1fb6-40f2-a447-e7362b9dc130\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T15:43:58.669Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"bytes\":264722,\"code\":200,\"codeText\":\"OK\",\"result\":\"# Resizing Detached tmux Sessions Headlessly\\n\\nBased on the GitHub issue #1367, here are the key findings:\\n\\n## The Problem\\nWhen a tmux session is detached, programmatic resize commands don't take effect until the session is reattached. The maintainer (nicm) explained: \\\"Resize happens on attach, not on detach. There is no way to explicitly set a size on an unattached session.\\\"\\n\\n## Proposed Solution\\nThe maintainer suggested using `force-width` and `force-height` parameters to set dimensions on unattached sessions immediately, without requiring an attach/detach cycle. The approach would be: \\\"make force-width/force-height set the size of any unattached sessions immediately.\\\"\\n\\n## Practical Workarounds\\nThe issue describes several attempted approaches:\\n- Using `resize-pane` with `-x` and `-y` flags\\n- Setting `aggressive-resize`, `force-height`, and `force-width` options\\n- Attempting to use `main-pane-height` and `main-pane-width`\\n\\nHowever, none of these achieve persistent sizing without reattachment.\\n\\n## Key Limitation\\nThe fundamental constraint is that tmux doesn't support explicit size specification for fully detached sessions without some form of client connection to trigger the resize operation.\",\"durationMs\":6388,\"url\":\"https://github.com/tmux/tmux/issues/1367\"},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"157dfc4a-fad5-431b-b375-4cd9495a14ce\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"27ee9bd0-1fb6-40f2-a447-e7362b9dc130\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_experiments\",\"sessionId\":\"e24bec4f-0ec1-4a86-bc8d-b2082f315a38\",\"version\":\"2.1.66\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/fix-droid-e2e-setup\",\"slug\":\"temporal-foraging-volcano\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01LqrGoyCZENd6dFSxjBaNR8\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"That's the root cause. tmux **cannot resize detached sessions** — the `-x`/`-y` on `new-session` and `resize-window` are both ignored because there's no attached client.\\n\\nThe workaround is to briefly attach a fake client with the desired size. Let me search for the exact trick:\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":423,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":129940,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":423},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYiJC1CvUjVJrJqoa2qkJ\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"742a0f73-f69a-462d-9005-569ab1bd426f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T15:44:04.355Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"742a0f73-f69a-462d-9005-569ab1bd426f\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_experiments\",\"sessionId\":\"e24bec4f-0ec1-4a86-bc8d-b2082f315a38\",\"version\":\"2.1.66\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/fix-droid-e2e-setup\",\"slug\":\"temporal-foraging-volcano\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01LqrGoyCZENd6dFSxjBaNR8\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_018Moe6YMtwCb752kvHs13Nw\",\"name\":\"WebSearch\",\"input\":{\"query\":\"tmux detached session set size workaround \\\"attach\\\" fake client headless resize\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":423,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":129940,\"output_tokens\":142,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":423,\"ephemeral_5m_input_