 for example: `tmux resize-window -x 122 -y 50`\\n\\n**Fake Client/Attach Workaround:** The moment you reattach to the fully-detached session, it will immediately resize, which is useful if you want to force a resize by temporarily attaching with desired dimensions.\\n\\n**ignore-size Flag:** The tmux client supports an `ignore-size` flag that makes the client not affect the size of other clients, which can be relevant for headless operations.\\n\\n**Detach-on-Attach Approach:** You can add the `-d` option to the attach-session command to make it detach elsewhere, which helps manage client sizing constraints.\\n\\nThe search results indicate this is a known limitation in tmux when working with detached sessions headlessly, particularly with control mode (`-CC`) clients. The practical workarounds involve either manually resizing windows or leveraging attach/detach cycles to trigger automatic resizing.\"],\"durationSeconds\":8.108012416999786},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"80f8dbad-8627-40a8-8cd8-5aa4a4b35013\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"261bb6ae-7af5-4541-abc1-9021b339661d\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_experiments\",\"sessionId\":\"e24bec4f-0ec1-4a86-bc8d-b2082f315a38\",\"version\":\"2.1.66\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/fix-droid-e2e-setup\",\"slug\":\"temporal-foraging-volcano\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01KPa1NGiUBFopTiseHrmfPq\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01Mq5Vkz3HUhUsGDpptcmrXn\",\"name\":\"WebFetch\",\"input\":{\"url\":\"https://github.com/tmux/tmux/issues/2063\",\"prompt\":\"What workaround was found for resizing a tmux pane in detached mode? Is there a way to set the size when creating the session that actually works?\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":949,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":130363,\"output_tokens\":119,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":949,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYiJDipjuv4x7o9drM2Ax\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"5dca7d77-cb90-432c-9fb0-93355fec98be\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T15:44:25.843Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"5dca7d77-cb90-432c-9fb0-93355fec98be\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_experiments\",\"sessionId\":\"e24bec4f-0ec1-4a86-bc8d-b2082f315a38\",\"version\":\"2.1.66\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/fix-droid-e2e-setup\",\"slug\":\"temporal-foraging-volcano\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01Mq5Vkz3HUhUsGDpptcmrXn\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"# Tmux Pane Resizing in Detached Mode\\n\\nBased on the GitHub issue discussion, **no definitive workaround was found** for the core problem.\\n\\n## What Was Attempted\\n\\nThe issue reporter and maintainer (nicm) explored several approaches:\\n\\n1. **SIGWINCH signals**: Testing `pkill -WINCH` or `kill -SIGWINCH` on the SSH process—this failed to resize the pane.\\n\\n2. **Initial sizing with `-x` and `-y`**: The user reported \\\"if I specify an initial size with `-x` and `-y` then it remains that size,\\\" indicating this approach doesn't adapt dynamically.\\n\\n3. **Manual attachment after creation**: Creating the session in detached mode worked differently than manual attachment, suggesting the problem was specific to the creation method rather than the session itself.\\n\\n## Root Cause Identified\\n\\nThe maintainer pinpointed the issue: when SSH starts in a detached tmux session via `send-keys`, the PTY initialization differs from manual SSH connections. The tmux status line resized correctly, but the SSH session within the pane did not receive proper resize signals.\\n\\n## Practical Recommendation\\n\\nThe issue remains closed without resolution. Users needing dynamic resizing should **attach to the session before initiating SSH connections** rather than automating them in detached mode.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"155e61dc-fbac-48b1-815c-96b46427c8f0\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T15:44:31.725Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"bytes\":282541,\"code\":200,\"codeText\":\"OK\",\"result\":\"# Tmux Pane Resizing in Detached Mode\\n\\nBased on the GitHub issue discussion, **no definitive workaround was found** for the core problem.\\n\\n## What Was Attempted\\n\\nThe issue reporter and maintainer (nicm) explored several approaches:\\n\\n1. **SIGWINCH signals**: Testing `pkill -WINCH` or `kill -SIGWINCH` on the SSH process—this failed to resize the pane.\\n\\n2. **Initial sizing with `-x` and `-y`**: The user reported \\\"if I specify an initial size with `-x` and `-y` then it remains that size,\\\" indicating this approach doesn't adapt dynamically.\\n\\n3. **Manual attachment after creation**: Creating the session in detached mode worked differently than manual attachment, suggesting the problem was specific to the creation method rather than the session itself.\\n\\n## Root Cause Identified\\n\\nThe maintainer pinpointed the issue: when SSH starts in a detached tmux session via `send-keys`, the PTY initialization differs from manual SSH connections. The tmux status line resized correctly, but the SSH session within the pane did not receive proper resize signals.\\n\\n## Practical Recommendation\\n\\nThe issue remains closed without resolution. Users needing dynamic resizing should **attach to the session before initiating SSH connections** rather than automating them in detached mode.\",\"durationMs\":5881,\"url\":\"https://github.com/tmux/tmux/issues/2063\"},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"5dca7d77-cb90-432c-9fb0-93355fec98be\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"155e61dc-fbac-48b1-815c-96b46427c8f0\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/User