cifies the width in columns\\n- `-y` specifies the height in rows\\n\\n## Important Notes:\\n\\nThe search results show that users have attempted various workarounds like using `resize-pane -t 0 -Z -x 80 -y 50`, setting `aggressive-resize on`, and using `force-height` and `force-width` options to properly size headless tmux sessions.\\n\\nYou can detach a session and it becomes a headless entity running in the background, allowing programs to continue running without a terminal attached.\\n\\nThe practical limitation is that tmux's size handling in detached mode can be unreliable, especially when other sessions are already attached to the server.\\n\\n\\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"f21f7b27-ffae-43ce-aefc-8503d9297e80\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T15:45:38.034Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"query\":\"tmux new-session \\\"-x\\\" \\\"-y\\\" size works detached headless example\",\"results\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"srvtoolu_01NyQhrSp3UxrYmxeBuu1xVV\",\"content\":[{\"title\":\"Headlessly resizing tmux window/session · Issue #1367 · tmux/tmux\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/tmux/tmux/issues/1367\"},{\"title\":\"Getting Started · tmux/tmux Wiki · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/tmux/tmux/wiki/Getting-Started\"},{\"title\":\"Tmux Cheat Sheet & Quick Reference | Session, window, pane and more\",\"url\":\"https://tmuxcheatsheet.com/\"},{\"title\":\"Detached new-session x/y is ignored if some other session is attached · Issue #4268 · tmux/tmux\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/tmux/tmux/issues/4268\"},{\"title\":\"How to Use tmux on Linux (and Why It's Better Than Screen)\",\"url\":\"https://www.howtogeek.com/671422/how-to-use-tmux-on-linux-and-why-its-better-than-screen/\"},{\"title\":\"A beginner's guide to tmux\",\"url\":\"https://www.redhat.com/en/blog/introduction-tmux-linux\"},{\"title\":\"A Quick and Easy Guide to tmux - Ham Vocke\",\"url\":\"https://hamvocke.com/blog/a-quick-and-easy-guide-