\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_experiments\",\"sessionId\":\"e24bec4f-0ec1-4a86-bc8d-b2082f315a38\",\"version\":\"2.1.66\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/fix-droid-e2e-setup\",\"slug\":\"temporal-foraging-volcano\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_0176dcgqCxvAMxEs47FQczeV\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01Y5ej2b7jxuc2uJyh2kgnM4\",\"name\":\"WebFetch\",\"input\":{\"url\":\"https://github.com/tmux/tmux/issues/4268\",\"prompt\":\"What is the issue? Does -x/-y on new-session work when NO other session is attached? What's the fix?\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":887,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":131735,\"output_tokens\":111,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":887,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYiJKLFMPUcefkvgoqwbQ\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"84fc4c8f-b60a-43d9-b87e-31af4a381829\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T15:45:42.332Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"84fc4c8f-b60a-43d9-b87e-31af4a381829\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_experiments\",\"sessionId\":\"e24bec4f-0ec1-4a86-bc8d-b2082f315a38\",\"version\":\"2.1.66\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/fix-droid-e2e-setup\",\"slug\":\"temporal-foraging-volcano\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01Y5ej2b7jxuc2uJyh2kgnM4\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"# TMux Issue #4268 Summary\\n\\n## The Problem\\n\\nWhen creating a detached tmux session with specified dimensions using `new-session -d -x 10 -y 10`, the width and height parameters are ignored if another session is already attached elsewhere. The new session incorrectly inherits the dimensions of the attached session instead.\\n\\n## Does -x/-y Work Without Other Sessions?\\n\\nYes. The issue reporter explicitly notes: \\\"The attached part is important, if you detach the issue can't be reproduced.\\\" This confirms that `-x` and `-y` flags work correctly when no other session is attached.\\n\\n## The Fix\\n\\nA tmux maintainer (nicm) provided a patch file (`x.diff.txt`) in response. The issue reporter confirmed it resolved the problem, stating: \\\"Looks like that does it, thanks!\\\" The patch was subsequently applied to the OpenBSD codebase and merged into the GitHub repository.\\n\\nThe underlying bug appears to be that tmux was incorrectly using the attached session's terminal dimensions rather than respecting the explicitly specified `-x` and `-y` parameters for newly created detached sessions.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"c5a484e4-90a4-48cb-bbf0-4284ebe58edd\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T15:45:49.296Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"bytes\":256311,\"code\":200,\"codeText\":\"OK\",\"result\":\"# TMux Issue #4268 Summary\\n\\n## The Problem\\n\\nWhen creating a detached tmux session with specified dimensions using `new-session -d -x 10 -y 10`, the width and height parameters are ignored if another session is already attached elsewhere. The new session incorrectly inherits the dimensions of the attached session instead.\\n\\n## Does -x/-y Work Without Other Sessions?\\n\\nYes. The issue reporter explicitly notes: \\\"The attached part is important, if you detach the issue can't be reproduced.\\\" This confirms that `-x` and `-y` flags work correctly when no other session is attached.\\n\\n## The Fix\\n\\nA tmux maintainer (nicm) provided a patch file (`x.diff.txt`) in response. The issue reporter confirmed it resolved the problem, stating: \\\"Looks like that does it, thanks!\\\" The patch was subsequently applied to the OpenBSD codebase and merged into the GitHub repository.\\n\\nThe underlying bug appears to be that tmux was incorrectly using t